<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<Weakness xmlns="http://cwe.mitre.org/cwe-7" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" ID="202" Name="Exposure of Sensitive Information Through Data Queries" Abstraction="Base" Structure="Simple" Status="Draft">
         <Description>When trying to keep information confidential, an attacker can often infer some of the information by using statistics.</Description>
         <Extended_Description>In situations where data should not be tied to individual users, but a large number of users should be able to make queries that "scrub" the identity of users, it may be possible to get information about a user -- e.g., by specifying search terms that are known to be unique to that user.</Extended_Description>
         <Related_Weaknesses>
            <Related_Weakness Nature="ChildOf" CWE_ID="1230" View_ID="1000" Ordinal="Primary" />
         </Related_Weaknesses>
